description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you looking for a new challenge? Are you ready for the move from a Band 5 to a Band 6? Ready to learn new skills? Please read on.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for an enthusiastic Part-time Audiologist to work within the Centre for Hearing and Balance Disorders here at University Hospitals Coventry and Warwickshire NHS Trust. The role could be worked over 4 half days or 2 full days depending on the preference of the successful applicant.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience in Tinnitus management is desirable for this role however we will train you if you have wish to specialise in this area but don&#39;t yet have the relevant experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please be advised that you must have NHS experience to apply for this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As this post involves carrying out home visits candidates must hold a valid UK driving licence and have access to a vehicle.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our department, which has maintained its UKAS accreditation for 7 years, offers the following services:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Adult Services include hearing aid fitting including complex services, diagnostic services, tinnitus rehabilitation and balance testing and rehabilitation. We liaise with a variety of services such as ENT, neurology and physiotherapy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Paediatric Services include a Newborn Hearing Screening Programme, diagnostic services and hearing aid clinics. We have excellent links with education and community services alongside an established Children’s Hearing Services Working Group.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Although this is predominantly an adult based role there will be an opportunity for you to be involved in paediatric assessment clinics in the community or at the hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are an established training site for PTP and STP students from Aston University. We serve a population of about 500,000 across Coventry and Rugby providing full adult and paediatric services. There are excellent road and good rail links for commuting.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We provide a monthly dedicated training session for all staff to provide opportunities to ensure your CPD is maintained.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name - Ann-Marie Hawkins&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title- Principal Adult Audiologist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address- ann-marie.hawkins@uhcw.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 02476 966444&lt;/p&gt;
